=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_NumChannels_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with square_like oscillator character around 101 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with evolving spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: evolving
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 100.5793
  harmonic_decay_rate: -19.0664
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8192
  pitch_clarity: 0.0000
  inharmonicity: 0.0027
  type: square_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -3.9636
  resonance_freq: 107.6660

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: NumChannels Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/NumChannels.html
// Tags: NumChannels, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
{
    NumChannels.ar(
        SinOsc.ar(100, 0, 0.2), // 1 becomes 2
        2)
}.play
)

(
{
    NumChannels.ar(
        SinOsc.ar([100, 200, 300], 0, 0.2), // 3 becomes 2
        2)
}.play
)

(
{
    NumChannels.ar(
        SinOsc.ar([100, 200, 300, 100], 0, 0.2), // 4 becomes 2

        2)
}.play
)
